Headquarters Regions: Greater New York Area, East Coast, Northeastern US
Full Description: Explore Brooklyn — developed by the Brooklyn Chamber of Commerce — is Brooklyn’s dedicated tourism website, a complete source for Brooklyn dining, events, shopping, attractions, and more. Under the leadership of Chamber president Carlo Scissura, Explore Brooklyn was created to foster economic growth by spreading the word to tourists and businesses alike that Brooklyn is the place to be. Explore Brooklyn is designed to help both New Yorkers and visitors find the best of Brooklyn all in one place, while giving local businesses and attractions an easy-to-use tool to promote themselves in a seamless social environment. The site is optimized for desktop, tablet, and mobile devices, and includes Brooklyn-centered editorial content written by some of the best bloggers in Brooklyn, a robust events calendar, and visually striking neighborhood pages. The central feature of the site, however, is a searchable directory of every business, restaurant, park, and point of interest in Brooklyn. This directory is populated with content that is dynamically gathered from Facebook, Google, Twitter, Foursquare, and many other sources around the web to create ready-made profiles that can then be customized by the business owner. Businesses and attractions on Explore Brooklyn can curate and showcase user reviews, maps, menus, photos, social network feeds, store hours, and more.

Description: Motion FX S.A. provides advanced products, services, and consulting to cinematographers, producers, broadcasters, and more.
Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, Silicon Valley, West Coast
Full Description: Motion FX S.A. provides advanced products, services, and consulting to cinematographers, producers, broadcasters, and post production facilities. The company was started primarily targeting the broadcasting, production, and post-production industry. In 2001, Motion FX S.A. along with a German company introduced the first direct to disk recording system designed for digital cinematography at International Broadcasting Convention in Amsterdam. In 2003, the company added new services as well as new product offerings to its product line. It participated in the production of the 2004 Special Olympics BBC opening themes. In 2005, the 4K film recording and the 2K color grading investment was the first new service that Motion FX S.A. added. By that time the company used the Silicon Color Final Touch 2K, that later became the Apple Color. In the same time it has developed its multi-camera iso.ingest direct to disk studio solution that sold to clients abroad. In 2007, Motion FX S.A. started to offer for clients around the world its innovative service for film recording. The idea was to transfer color management know-how-to partners abroad in order them to be able to do high-end 2k color grading with unsurpassed WYSIWYG for film-out with the new breed of tools from Apple. In 2008, Motion FX S.A. got the European Patent for its studio automation system, iso.ingest. The same time it started to develop a relay lens system for 2/3 cameras that allowed connecting low cost DoF to high-end 2/3 camcorders. In 2010 Motion FX S.A. have set up a network of 8 partners around the world, in Israel, Egypt, Belgium, Netherlands, and New York. It was established in 2000 by Evangelos Achillopoulos, Gaziano Roberto, Stijn Vanorbeek, and Artemios Achillopoulos.

Description: Ending Hunger Through Citizen Service.
Headquarters Regions: Greater New York Area, East Coast, Northeastern US
Full Description: In 2011, the latest data available, the USDA reported that more than 50 million Americans—including nearly 17 million children—lived in households that couldn’t afford enough food on a consistent basis throughout the year. The majority of food insecure or hungry Americans were working parents, children, senior citizens, veterans, and people with disabilities.   The good news is that effective citizen service—combined with improved public policies—can make a big difference. Working together, concerned individuals, civic organizations, youth groups, congregations, businesses, and elected officials can do their part to ensure that all Americans have access to sufficient, nutritious foods to ensure a healthful, active lifestyle.   Millions of Americans already generously give time and money to fight hunger, but they don’t always know the way to make the greatest impact. That is why ConAgra Foods and the New York City Coalition Against Hunger (NYCCAH) are spearheading a new nationwide initiative called “Ending Hunger Through Citizen Service.”   Starting with this web site, this effort includes concrete tools to help the public engage in volunteerism and for nonprofit groups to effectively harness the energy of such citizen service.
